        "Currently if someone does the following:\r\n\r\n```Python\r\nr.table(\"foo\").index_create(r.now())\r\n```\r\n\r\nThey'll get a constant index for the creation time which is pretty useless.\r\n\r\nInstead we should record the time each query is received in the global optargs and have `r.now()` evaluate to that value. This way that query does what users expect."
